prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "Display Google map view on the main screen",
      "evidence_quote": "This app consists of a Google map view on the main screen."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Provide multiple routes to reach destination from source with traffic and pollution status updates",
      "evidence_quote": "A user can select the source to destination path which then will be processed to give a number of routes to reach the destination from source with amount of traffic at various locations in that path along with current pollution status in that route (which updates overtime)."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow users to blow horn to all users within a specific radius",
      "evidence_quote": "If there exists a traffic jam, a user can blow a horn to all users within a specific radius."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Send notifications to users in specified radius when user blows horn",
      "evidence_quote": "According to his current location in the form of a small notification which the persons in the specified radius will receive."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow users to report accidents to concerned authority",
      "evidence_quote": "The accidents that occurred at specific spots will be reported by the user to the concerned authority who will do the rescue operations"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Categorize accident-prone areas based on number of accidents",
      "evidence_quote": "and a notification appears for the user to drive slow and safe when they are in that particular location."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Provide information about hotels and restaurants along chosen route",
      "evidence_quote": "Meals- on- wheel provides information about hotels and restaurants which are available in the chosen route so that the user can place the order as per the available menu at a particular eating place including time of service"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Send SMS to caller when driver is driving beyond speed limit",
      "evidence_quote": "This module would send an SMS to the caller that the particular person is driving when the geo- coordinates show the mobile shifting of the driver is beyond some specified speed limit (say, 20 kmph)"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow users to turn on drive-mode before start of journey",
      "evidence_quote": "Before start of the journey, this module can be turned on."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow users to give feedback about traffic and pollution levels in given area",
      "evidence_quote": "The feedback feature allows the user to give feedbacks about the accuracy in the traffic and pollution levels in a given area"
    }
  ]
}

llm_response:
Here is the rewritten requirements JSON:

```json
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "Display Google map view on the main screen",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall display a Google map view on the main screen."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Provide multiple routes to reach destination from source with traffic and pollution status updates",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall provide multiple routes to reach a destination from a source, including traffic and pollution status updates."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Allow users to blow horn to all users within a specific radius",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow users to blow a horn to all users within a specified radius."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Send notifications to users in specified radius when user blows horn",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall send notifications to users within a specified radius when a user blows their horn."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Allow users to report accidents to concerned authority",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow users to report accidents to the concerned authorities."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Categorize accident-prone areas based on number of accidents",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall categorize areas prone to accidents based on the number of accidents that have occurred there."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Provide information about hotels and restaurants along chosen route",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall provide information about hotels and restaurants available along a chosen route."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Send SMS to caller when driver is driving beyond speed limit",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall send an SMS to the caller when a driver is traveling beyond a specified speed limit."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Allow users to turn on drive-mode before start of journey",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow users to enable drive mode before starting their journey."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Allow users to give feedback about traffic and pollution levels in given area",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow users to provide feedback on the accuracy of traffic and pollution levels in a specific area."
    }
  ]
}
```
